Tom, Cook, I must admit you two are beyond me on this, and I will leave it to you. Perhaps I mirror the average American in this, that I tought Viet Nam was one country, divided in Geneva into two, and that the North wanted it re-unified, but the South, under the control of the USA and others, didn't. Is that an over simply understanding?<br><br>
Seems the North had a purpose of mission while the South had corruption.  I don't know what the average peasant wanted except to be left alone and not murdered by either side.  What would have happened if we (the USA) had not gone in at all?  Seems to me that we wasted our blood, and that lesson is the most important, not who is the strongest and macho marine, or who is more historically accurate.  <br><br>
I listen to the both of you, and I fear that I see it happening all over again.  Tom, you I know and I know you are not of that camp. Cook, you I don't know, but it seems that your pride and honor could get alot of folks killed all over again.   Go ahead, guys, I can take a few more hits, so let loose.<br><br>
